  "commentary": "With SPX spot at 6564.65 sitting right in the heart of massive negative gamma between 6550-6570 (all showing -24M to -44M), dealers are likely buying this move higher as they're short gamma in this zone, which creates amplifying pressure that should fuel continued upside momentum. The breakout regime with -207B total GEX confirms dealers will chase this rally, and with max positive gamma resistance not until 6600 (+18B), we have runway for trending moves higher with dealers as fuel rather than friction. Key level is defending 6550 (-44B max neg gamma) on any pullback - break below and dealers flip to selling, but holding above keeps the amplifying bid intact toward 6600 where they'll start selling into strength.\n\nBottom line: expect continued upside momentum with dealer buying supporting the move toward 6600.",
